# Documentation Guidelines

When editing documentation, **only modify files in `docs/sphinx/`**, not `docs/*.md` directly.

## Directory Structure

- `docs/sphinx/*.md` - **Source files** (edit these)
- `docs/*.md` - **Auto-generated** from sphinx build (do not edit directly)
- `docs/sphinx/_build/` - Build output (do not edit)

## Workflow

1. Edit source files in `docs/sphinx/`
2. Run `make markdown` from `docs/` to regenerate `docs/*.md`
3. The root `docs/*.md` files are auto-generated and will be overwritten

## Important

- Never edit `docs/cli-reference.md`, `docs/examples.md`, `docs/index.md`, or `docs/installation.md` directly
- These files contain an auto-generated warning comment at the top
- All documentation changes should be made in `docs/sphinx/` source files
